{
  "description": "Classification of the 98 nearby-range candidates that changed between two scans ~30 min apart while idling. single_bit_flip = exactly one bit differs between the two captures - the strongest, cheapest-to-verify signal (this is how 1147 bit4 and 1148 bit5 were found), but note this is a heuristic, not proof: 110A (TPS, a known analog PID) also produced a single-bit-looking delta purely by coincidence, so treat single-bit hits as priority candidates for direct on/off correlation testing, not confirmed flags. small_drift = changed by a small amount in both directions, consistent with continuous analog sensor noise (this is where RPM, TPS, and battery voltage land). large_jump = changed by a lot - could be counters, timers, multi-byte values, or just unclear without more data.",
  "next_step": "For each single_bit_flip candidate (excluding already_known_pid ones), watch it live while deliberately toggling something physical, the same way 1147 bit4 (A/C request) and 1148 bit5 (purge valve, found via idle-time drift) were confirmed.",
